Patients at the fever clinic at Tongji Hospital in Wuhan on the evening of February 2. Photo by Zheng Li, reporter of Zhongqingbao Zhongqingnet

Fang Lu (not her real name) is a 34-year-old Wuhan resident. After her in-laws were admitted to hospital with pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection, she began to organize "self-help" among "patients" through wechat groups. Every day, she posts official information in her group, updating them on the progress of the epidemic and answering questions about symptoms. She created an open form where people in need could fill in information and forward it when the opportunity presented itself, whether it was waiting in line for a nucleic acid test or a hospital bed.

She now lives at home with her 7-year-old son. The husband, who had been in contact with her in laws, had voluntarily quarantined himself in the hotel for two weeks.
On the day before New Year's Eve, she did a "big shopping" , after which she and her son did not leave the house.

By Fang Lu

I wasn't prepared for any of this.

From January 13 to 16, I took my kids to a free winter camp organized by the government, with skiing, skating and other winter sports classes. I also enrolled my kids in an indoor skiing program. It rarely snows in Wuhan.

On January 17th I came across an article titled Virus Chronicle in Wuhan -- The first outbreak in 2020.

January 18, the children's winter vacation class is all over, the husband asked where to play winter vacation? I gave him a blank look. What'd I do? Now want to travel abroad, too late to apply for a visa? When I suggested the route of the Shennongjia International Ski Resort, my husband was too cold to enjoy it.

On the night of January 19, my body suddenly felt strange and I coughed for no reason. If it is normal, cough twice is not normal? But at this moment, these two sounds actually remind me of the article I saw before. Before going to bed, my husband said he had a fever, and his temperature was 100 degrees. I was a little surprised, but I quickly realized that what was on the news wasn't going to happen to me.

January 20, mother-in-law sent us to pay attention to the "virus infection" message. I was still thinking about going skiing, and sent out a friend's circle to collect people's opinions on "should we go out to play? ". Someone replied, "never mind. It's too dangerous. ". Some people say they can play if they want. My friend encouraged me that my son was in charge and could play however he wanted! That's the answer I'm looking for.

Make a decision, I call her mother-in-law informed, the result she said, father-in-law fever for a few days, not down, oneself also feel sick, tomorrow to the community to prescribe some medicine. I think back to the news and Internet articles I have seen in the past few days. I asked my mother-in-law not to deal with them casually. I had a check-up to rule out the possibility of "that disease" . Mother-in-law did not answer, obviously want to carry again. Old People are like this, usually have a headache hot, are their own prescription. They thought it would cost too much to go to the hospital, and even a casual examination would cost hundreds of dollars.

The other day I was driving out on an errand, and I felt really tired on the way. I can fall asleep for two seconds at a red light, or even when there are fewer cars on the viaduct. My husband said his temperature was 103, and that his co worker and his mother were in the hospital because of viral pneumonia.

January 21, the husband on a whim to the market to buy half a chicken, but also casually told a "joke" , said to buy food today, a stall is empty, other stall owners said, "because of the disease shut in the SA. At the time, we didn't think it had anything to do with us.

The chicken soup is not ready yet, the mother-in-law called, said the father-in-law has not reduced fever. The soup just rises wok, the mother-in-law's telephone came again, asked when the husband can go, obviously was anxious. Mother-in-law usually have what one shoulder, rarely let us know, and rarely asked us to help her, visible not good.

Husband rushed over, who knows this, he can not come back to live.

That night, my husband called me anxiously, saying that he took my father in law to the third hospital for a check up. The CT results showed viral pneumonia. I calm down, told him to take the old man home first, two rooms, "you do not come back, in my parents home near a hotel, tomorrow take my mother to check. ".

Settle the parents, 2 o'clock in the morning, he called me, with a cry asked: "This Disease Will Not die? " I said, not diagnosed, do not think so much, if you fall, who sent your parents to the hospital for examination? What if I take the three of you to the hospital and the baby?

On January 22, the mother-in-law had a test, and the results were viral pneumonia, but not the "disease, " which requires a kit for nucleic acid testing. That day, I saved the winter did not wash the home sweater coat, bedspread, high-temperature washing, drying, washing the whole day, there are 2 barrels of washing. I also spent the day scrolling through my friends and feeds, going through all the articles about viral pneumonia, obscurely, probably on the news, as a way of dealing with my stress so I didn't have time to worry and be afraid.

Because my parents-in-law haven't been diagnosed yet, and I'm afraid to tell anyone. In my friend circle still has some old man's friend, in case the examination result is not "that sickness" , hereafter the neighbor all eludes us to walk, is not good. At this time, the severity of the epidemic, has been known, but the people around us, our family may be the first, my friends think, this is a distant thing, other people's things.

In the evening, my mother-in-law called, and she sounded like she had just cried. She said she hurt her son, that she shouldn't have sent him there, that she dragged him down with her. The old couple plan to save a lifetime of savings to me, if they three people can not pass this hurdle, I must be strong, bring up the child. I tried to tell her there was a hole in the test results, to comfort her, maybe not!

My husband slept alone in the hotel, and was too scared to sleep, and then called me in the middle of the night, crying that there would be no mom and dad. I told him to reassure the elderly so they could focus on their care, that we could plan for the worst and then think about the "future. ". The husband gave a loud hiss. I said, go to sleep, if you don't, they have no hope of surviving, you must be strong, protect yourself, tomorrow to do the test. I've been comforting them like this every day since.

On January 23, I continued to wash the clothes I hadn't finished the day before, making myself feel like I was doing a lot of work. Now recalled, but do not know what in the end of their busy.

In the afternoon, I received two confirmation letters from my parents-in-law, and then I ran into a problem that continues to plague new cases of pneumonia: no beds. Three hospitals the first day, fever clinics the next day. Then went to the People's Hospital, fever clinic also closed. Mother-in-law said she left her contact information early, and to seven hospitals, nine hospitals, Wuchang Hospital call, unexpectedly full beds.

From that day on, I repeatedly posted a request for help on my friends'network. As in my previous case, everyone thought my experience was strange: "there are cases of this happening to acquaintances. ". Even though I specifically asked not to, I spent the entire evening on the phone, and everyone was trying to help the unfortunate guy, so much so that I haven't responded to any messages that actually helped. At the time, all I cared about was where the beds were, and whether my contacts could get me a bed. Hearing that the other party can not help, I will even be impatient, thinking, busy, more delay!

We did not just start to find a bed, from the first day to get my father-in-law's diagnosis, my husband on the search for help, did not think bed so difficult. Who knows? Three days later, we scoured every resource we could reach, everyone we knew came back, and there was nothing we could do about it. My mother-in-law called me anxiously to say that she was really desperate. On the night of the 23rd, after a whole day's hard work, two doctors at the hospital finally said, my in-laws are seriously ill, help us to find a way. In the early morning of the 24th, my mother-in-law called to say that one of the doctors could not be reached. I comforted her. It's okay. There's another one. Soon, the only doctor left said there was nothing to be done. I appreciate it. At least I got a good night's sleep.

On January 24, New Year's Eve, just when we were feeling down and out of the blue, two beds appeared. I do not feel a bit of the taste of the new year, no one set up a New Year's dinner, a family scattered in different places, everyone feels particularly bleak. I and the child at home, did not see the Spring Festival gala, before the ready goods, have not in the mood to eat. I still remember half a month ago, I and my husband in bed watching "Qingyunian" , Badabada ate one night, my husband laughed at me a person finished 3 jins of Emperor Tangerine, I laugh at my husband eating peanuts like a mouse in a jar of rice. But New Year's Eve, accompanied by me only tired and full of soreness. Fortunately, the husband got the test results, "negative. ". I don't have to check, because work is busy, I haven't been to the in-laws for half a month.

Since my husband left on the 21st, I've been in high gear. After New Year's Eve, I slept soundly for two days. In-laws into the hospital I rest assured that the package, treatment in the doctor, there is nothing to worry about, I even did not ask the illness, think it will be better and better.

Then I learned that my father-in-law had a high fever after he was admitted to the hospital. His fever was so high that his mother-in-law was worried that he had not slept well all night. Later, the father-in-law's body temperature finally drops down, finally lets the human put down a hanging heart. Mother-in-law has been a hundred times energetic, not like a sick person, the doctor was supposed to give her to reduce drugs ready to discharge, but she continued high fever. COVID-19 is so elusive that even doctors have no idea what a full course of treatment is supposed to look like. Mother-in-law fever for 2 days, the temperature began to fall, I thought that can always rest assured, the result of her husband always feel chest tightness, and went to check the CT, but was suspected of early lung cancer... This Day Day ups and downs, the writers dare not write.

On January 27, I clicked on a message from a long-lost Wuhan University of Technology Alumnus who said her husband was "highly suspicious. ". Her husband is also my alum, their daughter's picture, I often see in friends circle, really beautiful AH, inherited my mother's minority gene. As a mother, I couldn't let them go.

At the time, nucleic acid test kits were in short supply, like handing out five red packets to a crowd of 100 people, which you might never get.

Because I had posted a request for help, a lot of people knew I had a patient in my home, and almost every day, friends I knew or didn't know came to me asking if this was COVID-19 pneumonia and if that was all that mattered. I know what it's like to face the unknown, the stakes of life and death.

I can't wait for someone to tell me what it's like? What's GonNa Happen? What's the next step? No one knows for sure. As experiencers, we are at the center of the information, and in the midst of all the rumors, refutations, and counter-rumors, only what we experience is true. After the city was shut down, some people left us for good before they were diagnosed. To defeat this terrible virus, we must save ourselves, and we must unite. I quickly set up a group of patients, I hope to get the information I want from others, also hope to distribute their own resources to them. I can't just stand by and watch this happen.

Every day, I spend a lot of time to bring people together and hope that they can help themselves. I wake up every day thinking about how many people in my group haven't had their nucleic acid tested yet. I have a famous "chicken soup story" in my head -- like a little boy picking up fish on the beach and throwing them back into the sea. You can't help all the fish. The little boy said, yes, but I can help this one, this one, and this one..
